{"kind":"symbol","variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"occ"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset"]}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"symbolKind":"property","title":"centerOffset","roleHeading":"Instance Property","externalID":"c:objc(cs)MLNAnnotationView(py)centerOffset","role":"symbol","remoteSource":{"fileName":"MLNAnnotationView.h","url":"https:\/\/github.com\/maplibre\/maplibre-native\/blob\/main\/platform\/ios\/src\/MLNAnnotationView.h#L159"},"fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"}]},"primaryContentSections":[{"declarations":[{"tokens":[{"text":"@property","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":" ("},{"text":"nonatomic","kind":"keyword"},{"kind":"text","text":") "},{"text":"CGVector","preciseIdentifier":"c:@S@CGVector","kind":"typeIdentifier"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"centerOffset","kind":"identifier"},{"text":";","kind":"text"}],"languages":["occ"],"platforms":["iOS"]}],"kind":"declarations"},{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"By default, the center point of an annotation view is placed at the geographic","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"coordinate point of the associated annotation. If you do not want the view to","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"be centered, you can use this property to reposition the view. The offset’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dy"},{"type":"text","text":" values are measured in points. Positive offset values move the"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"annotation view down and to the right, while negative values move it up and to"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the left."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Set the offset if the annotation view’s visual center point is somewhere other","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"than the logical center of the view. For example, the view may contain an image","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"that depicts a downward-pointing pushpin or thumbtack, with the tip positioned"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"at the center-bottom of the view. In that case, you would set the offset’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"dx"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"to zero and its ","type":"text"},{"code":"dy","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" to half the height of the view."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","interfaceLanguage":"occ"},"abstract":[{"text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view.","type":"text"}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView"]]},"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"sections":[],"references":{"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre":{"role":"collection","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"Powerful, free and open-source mapping toolkit with full control over data sources and styling."}],"title":"MapLibre","kind":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre"},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView/centerOffset":{"kind":"symbol","role":"symbol","type":"topic","title":"centerOffset","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview\/centeroffset","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"The offset, measured in points, at which to place the center of the view."}],"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView\/centerOffset","fragments":[{"kind":"identifier","text":"centerOffset"}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotationView":{"kind":"symbol","title":"MLNAnnotationView","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotationview","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotationView","kind":"identifier"}],"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotationView","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" class is responsible for marking a point annotation"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"with a view. Annotation views represent an annotation object, which is an"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"object that corresponds to the "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" protocol. When an annotation’s"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"geographic coordinate is visible in the map view, the map view asks its"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"delegate to a corresponding annotation view. If an annotation view is created"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"with a reuse identifier, the map view may recycle the view when it goes","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"offscreen."}]},"doc://org.swift.MyProject/documentation/MapLibre/MLNAnnotation":{"abstract":[{"text":"The ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation"},{"text":" protocol is used to provide annotation-related information","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"to a map view. To use this protocol, you adopt it in any custom objects that","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"store or represent annotation data. Each object then serves as the source of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"information about a single map annotation and provides critical information,","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"such as the annotation’s location on the map. Annotation objects do not provide","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"the visual representation of the annotation but typically coordinate (in","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"conjunction with the map view’s delegate) the creation of an appropriate","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"objects to handle the display.","type":"text"}],"kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/maplibre\/mlnannotation","role":"symbol","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNAnnotation","fragments":[{"text":"MLNAnnotation","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"MLNAnnotation"}}}